"""
server.py — FastAPI Real-Time Inference Server

NOTE: This module currently exposes a legacy churn-oriented API surface from the
original reusable monitoring-core phase of the repository. The repo’s primary
identity is now battery/BMS-first; this server remains as a reference serving
example until a dedicated BMS API surface fully replaces it.

Replaces the batch CSV simulation with a live HTTP API.

Endpoints
─────────
POST /predict          Score a single customer record; returns churn probability
POST /predict/batch    Score a list of records in one call
GET  /health           Liveness probe — returns model status + system metrics
GET  /metrics          Current sliding-window drift + ROI snapshot
GET  /window/stats     Distribution statistics for the current feature window
DELETE /window/reset   Clear the feature buffer (useful for testing)

Architecture
────────────
Every prediction request:
  1. Validates input schema (Pydantic)
  2. Passes features to the loaded sklearn Pipeline
  3. Logs the raw features + prediction into a thread-safe sliding window
  4. Returns probability + latency

Every 500 requests (configurable) the background drift checker:
  1. Pulls the window snapshot
  2. Runs DriftDetector.detect() against the reference distribution
  3. Computes ROI impact of current AUC estimate
  4. Appends result to server_drift_log.json
  5. Fires an alert if severity is warning/critical

Run locally
───────────
    uvicorn src.api.server:app --reload --port 8000

Then send a test prediction:
    curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/predict \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d '{"tenure":6,"monthly_charges":85,"total_charges":510,
           "num_products":1,"num_support_calls":5,"avg_call_duration":12,
           "days_since_last_login":45,"data_usage_gb":8.5,
           "billing_amount_variance":12,"customer_lifetime_value":2100,
           "contract_type":"Month-to-month","payment_method":"Electronic check",
           "internet_service":"Fiber optic","tech_support":"No",
           "online_security":"No","paperless_billing":"Yes"}'
"""

